line: It all makes sense. The money in the briefcase, they've been conducting an experiment here. Somebody's been paying to have those kids injected with alien DNA to see how they'd react. It's been going on for years.

speaker: SCULLY
line: Does that man know anything about it?

speaker: MULDER
line: No. He's just some poor soul who blew their cover. I don't think he knows any more than he's telling us.

speaker: SCULLY
line: Well, I think his boss must have because they just found him shot to death in a cow pasture.

speaker: MULDER
line: What?

speaker: SCULLY
line: I think I know who shot him, Mulder. That man that I recognized on the road today... that's the same man that executed Deep Throat.

speaker: MULDER
line: Well, whoever's behind this, he's here covering their tracks. He's going to go after the kids. You get the sheriff and meet me at Gary Kane's apartment. And, Scully... I want this guy alive.

speaker: MULDER
line: Where's Gary?

speaker: BETH KANE
line: He's in his bedroom.

speaker: MULDER
line: Go pack some clothes, things you need. You're all coming with me.

speaker: BETH KANE
line: What?

speaker: MULDER
line: I'll explain later. Those credit card numbers, every kid's family that was listed. Get them packed up. Call out every man you've got.

speaker: MAZEROSKI
line: Where are we taking them?

speaker: ODIN
line: Yes?

speaker: MULDER
line: I need your help.

speaker: ODIN
line: For?

speaker: MULDER
line: It may offend your religious sensibilities but it could help save some kids' lives.

speaker: SCULLY
line: Sheriff... where's Mulder?

speaker: MAZEROSKI
line: He told me to make sure that the kids were safe. He thought there was some other place this guy might be.

speaker: MULDER
line: Stop right there! Hey!

speaker: SCULLY
line: Don't move! Put it down. Now. Just put the lighter down.

speaker: MULDER
line: Hey! Get him out of here. Get everyone out of here!

speaker: DEPUTY
line: Come on.

speaker: SCULLY
line: File number XWC060361. The identity of the man shot in the slaughterhouse has yet to be determined. His name, any record or artifact of his past, present or immigration status have yet to be found. His fingerprints are not on file in either the F.B.I. or National System of Records. At this time, it remains doubtful that anyone will come forward to I.D. or claim the body.

speaker: SCULLY
line: Under further analysis, the inoculant found in the broken vials was isolated and determined to be an unstable antibody of no known biological origin. After three weeks of study, the components of the serum, probably synthetic, have broken down structurally and, in this retrograde state, cannot be analyzed further. This coincides with the development of a severe and undiagnosed flu-like ailment affecting the children who were believed to be inoculated and some of the local families. To date, none of the congregants or members of the Church of the Red Museum have contracted this illness. I suspect whoever was doing may have been using them as a control group. The shipping manifests for what is believed to be milk and beef tainted by the unspecified inoculant do not provide enough information to track their destinations. A local advisory and quarantine have been established. Further inquiry into the tainted beef has been promised by the pertinent government health agencies. The F.B.I. investigation into this case is currently at a standstill. The case remains open and unsolved.
